<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05034f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05034f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05034f"> 34(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chatting about heaven</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Emperor sent often for the Saint to come and talk to him, consulted him in his undertakings, asked him for advice about his conduct, talked with him of his future life, the glory of the redeemed, and of eternity and its attendant hopes and fears. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 60-61</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
